# Interactive Help Messages

Help.IconBar:\TCrosses application.|MIt plays Noughts and Crosses.|M\Sstart a new game.

Help.Main:\Tmain Crosses \w.|MIt plays the game of Noughts and Crosses.
Help.Main.Grid:\Sto place an X or an O on the playing grid.
Help.Main.Display:\Tinformation field.|MWatch the text for details of the game's progress.
Help.Main.XScore:\Tscore for the player with X.
Help.Main.OScore:\Tscore for the player with O.
Help.Main.Score:\Tscoreboard.|MDepending on the configured options, it may also count the games that have been played.

Help.Choices:\TChoices \w for Crosses.|MIt allows aspects of the game to be configured.
Help.Choices.Set:\Sset the options for the current session and close the \w.|M\Aset the options and leave the \w open.
Help.Choices.Cancel:\Sclose the \w and forget any changes made.|M\Areset any changes and leave the \w open.
Help.Choices.XNameOpt:\Schoose whether a name can be set for the player for X.
Help.Choices.ONameOpt:\Schoose whether a name can be set for the player for O.
Help.Choices.XName:\Tname of the player for X.
Help.Choices.OName:\Tname of the player for O.
Help.Choices.OComp:\Schoose whether O will be played by a human or the computer.
Help.Choices.Draws:\Schoose whether drawn games are counted in the scoreboard.|MIf yes, they will be attributed to both players.
Help.Choices.Count:\Schoose whether the game count will be shown in the scoreboard.
Help.Choices.3D:\Sselect a 2D or 3D game.|M2D is a standard 3 by 3 grid.|M3D is three 3 by 3 grids stacked on top of each other.

Help.Info:\Tprogram information \w for the Crosses application.
Help.Info.Website:\Tprogram information \w for the Crosses application.|M\Svisit its website for information and updates.

Help.MainMenu.00:\Sstart a new game.
Help.MainMenu.01:\Sreset the scoreboard.

Help.IconBarMenu.00:\Rto see information about Crosses and visit its website.
Help.IconBarMenu.01:\Sread the Crosses documentation.
Help.IconBarMenu.02:\Schange the settings for Crosses.
Help.IconBarMenu.03:\Squit Crosses.


